  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of the Road Sector Programme Support, Phase 2 was to support the national road sector development plan with the main emphasis on the creation of sustainable road administrations and funding mechanisms for development and maintenance of all levels of roads. The programme used labour based methods to address poverty through creating job opportunities for the rural population and by targeting vulnerable groups as labourers. The programme also trained workers who can be used for future road maintenance activities. Part of the support was earmarked to 15 districts in Northern Uganda and the main focus being to construct and improve the road network to strengthen transport connections in the rural areas.

The programme was initially planned to be implemented from 2003 to 2007 but the completion was extended to June 2010. Heavy rains and flooding during the latter part of 2007 caused damage to some of the already completed construction works while some of the unfinished constructions were delayed.</narrative>
  </description>
